    "observations": "CYP2C9 and CYP2C19 have significant impacts on Vm and Km.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Simplified PK",
    "equations": "GTVm = theta4**G4 GTKm = theta5**G2+theta6**G3 Vm = theta1*((WT/60)**theta3)*GTVm*(1+eta1) Km = theta2*GTKm*(1+eta2) DD=(Vm*Css)/(F*(Km+Css))*(1+eps1) G2 is belonging to genetic group 2 (0=no; 1=yes) G3 is belonging to genetic group 3 (0=no; 1=yes) G4 is belonging to genetic group 4 (0=no; 1=yes) F is bioavailability (fixed to 1 here) Formulae were converted from mg/day/kg to mg/day for ease of use. The additive error term eps1 was also converted, using the typical Vm, Km, and Css (6.07, 4.0, and 7.8 respectively)",
